The dFC states of interest were then finally submitted to a modularity analysis, with the purpose of identifying modular (or community) structure in those states. Because the dFC states are column vectors, rather than square matrices representing a connectivity matrix as required for the modularity analysis, such connectivity matrix of a given dFC state \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
